<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Bryan</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October 6,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 296.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your telegram of the 27th
                            ultimo, stating that the Thomsen case had been settled, I now take
                            pleasure in transmitting a copy of an appreciative letter from Messrs.
                            Dickerson, Brown &amp; Raegener, Mr. Thomsen’s attorneys.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg></opener>
                            <head><hi rend="italic"><persName type="from">Dickerson, Brown &amp;
                                        Raegener</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                            York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-10-01"><hi rend="italic">October 1,
                                        1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In the name of our client, Mr. H. A.
                                Thomsen, and in our own behalf, we hereby express our thanks to the
                                Department of State and to the United States minister to Brazil for
                                their prompt and energetic assistance, without which a settlement
                                would have been impossible and but for which a valuable business
                                would have been ruined.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor, etc.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dickerson, Brown &amp;
                                        Raegener.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>